children.subject: Very biased and haven't taken 186, but would definitely recommend that everyone takes 161. If you are ever going to be building products that real people are going to use, it's really important to be aware of how privacy leakages are possible and how to write code that's resilient against attack.

Also biased - 161 is definitely more useful for SWE because it also covers the most useful portions of 168 and 169. I liked 186 as a class, but imo, the content isn't very applicable for the vast majority of SWE positions, and its strongest point is getting experience working with larger codebases.

history.content: I can't decide between taking CS 161 or CS 186. Any idea which is more useful? For reference, I am a CS major primarily interested in datascience and machine learning, however I will likely end up in a SWE position.
history.subject: CS 161 or CS 186
